<p><span fontWeight='bold' color='#0000FF'>动词</span></p>
<p><span color='#0000FF'>用这些动词来表明你非常确定你说的东西：</span></p>
<p><span fontWeight='bold'>have to, must, need to, should, shall, will</span></p>
<p><span fontStyle="italic">Doing this </span><span fontWeight='bold' fontStyle="italic">will</span> <span fontStyle="italic">improve the situation.</span></p> 
<p><span color='#0000FF'>用这些动词来说明一些很可能发生但并不完全确定的事：</span></p>
<p><span fontWeight='bold'>may, might, can, could, ought to</span></p>
<p><span fontStyle="italic">A bully </span><span fontWeight='bold' fontStyle="italic">might</span> <span fontStyle="italic">feel lonely.</span></p> 
<p><span fontWeight='bold' color='#0000FF'>副词</span></p>
<p><span color='#0000FF'>这些副词强烈表达出你的想法：</span></p>
<p><span fontWeight='bold'>clearly, obviously, in fact, of course, certainly</span></p>
<p><span fontStyle="italic">Doing this will </span><span fontWeight='bold' fontStyle="italic">certainly</span><span fontStyle="italic"> improve the situation.</span></p>
<p><span color='#0000FF'>用这些副词表示某事通常发生，但不绝对。</span></p>
<p><span fontWeight='bold'>often, frequently, typically, normally, usually, generally</span></p>
<p><span fontStyle="italic">Bullies </span><span fontWeight='bold' fontStyle="italic">usually</span> <span fontStyle="italic">attack someone who they think is weak.</span></p> 
<p><span color='#0000FF'>亦见</span><span fontWeight='bold'>sudden</span>条的写作提示。</p> 

